article.headline: Arizona 79, Washington St. 72
article.story:
LOS ANGELES -- Ify Ebekwe had 23 points and 14 rebounds, Courtney Clements added 19 and Arizona defeated Washington State 79-72 in a first-round game of the Pac-10 tournament Thursday night. No. 9 seed Arizona will face No. 2 Stanford in a quarterfinal game on Friday.

The ninth-seeded Wildcats are 0-2 in both meetings against Stanford this season, but lost their last game to the Cardinal one week ago by only three points.

No. 8 seed Washington State and Arizona traded baskets in a second half that had four ties and eight lead changes, but the Wildcats hit key shots down the stretch. Ashley Frazier hit a 3-pointer with 6:52 remaining to give Arizona (12-18) the lead for good, 63-60, and Clements added a 3 with 1:50 remaining.

April Cook had two 3s for the Cougars (11-19) with less than 40 seconds remaining to bring Washington State within four, but Reiko Thomas and Clements combined to hit five free throws to finish the game.

Cook led the Cougars with 22 points.

Washington State went without a basket for nearly five minutes until Ebonee Coates hit a layup with 2:53 remaining.

Katie Appleton had 14 for the Cougars, including four 3s.

Amina Njonkou added 15 points and eight rebounds for Arizona.

The Wildcats put together the most wins (12) since the 2004-05 season, when Arizona went 20-12 and lost in the second round of the NCAA tournament.

Arizona got off to a slow start and the Wildcats fell behind 28-17 in the first half when Washington State hit four consecutive 3s to cap a 14-4 run.

Appleton had three of those treys, all within a 1:10 span.

The Wildcats answered with a 14-2 run of their own, mostly behind Clements. The freshman guard from Long Beach sparked the run with a fastbreak at 7:44 and hit a 3 and two jumpers before knocking down a free throw to tie the game at 30. Both teams traded baskets until Ibekwe hit a jumper to take a 37-35 halftime lead.

Jazmine Perkins, the Pac-10's leading freshman scorer all season with 13.9, was limited to 10 against Arizona.
